message.content:
I need to calculate two financial ratios based on the provided financial statements: Quick Ratio and Net Profit Margin.

## Quick Ratio
The Quick Ratio = (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities

From the balance sheet:
- Current Assets = $10,261,562.67
- Inventory = $430,000.00
- Current Liabilities = $1,548,001.20

Quick Ratio = (10,261,562.67 - 430,000.00) / 1,548,001.20
Quick Ratio = 9,831,562.67 / 1,548,001.20
Quick Ratio = 6.35

## Net Profit Margin
The Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%

From the income statement:
- Net Profit = $1,105,265.77
- Total Revenue = $5,760,023.09

Net Profit Margin = (1,105,265.77 / 5,760,023.09) × 100%
Net Profit Margin = 0.1919 × 100%
Net Profit Margin = 19.19%

{"solution": {'Quick Ratio': '6.35', 'Net Profit Margin': '19.19%'}}
